UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 77
1 (7) Develop plans that may be required by federal legislation. The council shall for all
2 purposes of federal legislation relating to planning be considered the "single state
3 agency" as that term may be used in federal legislation. When federal legislation
4 requires additional representation on any "single state agency," the Council on
5 Postsecondary Education shall establish advisory groups necessary to satisfy federal
6 legislative or regulatory guidelines;
7 (8) (a) Determine tuition and mandatory student fees and approve the minimum
8 qualifications for admission to the state postsecondary educational system in
9 accordance with the following:
10 1. Tuition and mandatory student fees shall not be increased for any
11 program more than five percent (5%) in any one (1) year for incoming
12 Kentucky resident students and seven percent (7%) in any one (1) year
13 for non-Kentucky resident students without approval from the General
14 Assembly;
15 2. Tuition and mandatory student fees at the University of Louisville, the
16 University of Kentucky, and the comprehensive universities shall not
17 be increased for a Kentucky resident student unless the student:
18 a. Completes four (4) years of continuous enrollment at the
19 institution;
20 b. Graduates from a baccalaureate or graduate program at the
21 institution; or
22 c. Fails to maintain continuous enrollment;
23 3. If a Kentucky resident student remains enrolled at the University of
24 Louisville, the University of Kentucky, or a comprehensive university
25 after four (4) years, the tuition and mandatory student fees charged to
26 the student by that institution for any subsequent term in the program
27 shall not exceed the amount of tuition and mandatory student fees for
Page 2 of 11
XXXX 1/14/2026 10:22 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 77
1 an incoming Kentucky resident student in the same program that
2 term;
3 4. If a Kentucky resident student fails to maintain continuous enrollment
4 at the University of Louisville, the University of Kentucky, or a
5 comprehensive university, the tuition and mandatory student fees
6 charged to the student for any subsequent term in that program shall
7 not exceed the amount of tuition and mandatory student fees for an
8 incoming Kentucky resident student in the same program that term;
9 5. An institution shall notify any non-Kentucky resident student or
10 continuing Kentucky resident student of any increase in tuition or
11 mandatory student fees that would impact the student at least four (4)
12 months prior to the effective date of the increase;
13 6. An increase in tuition and mandatory student fees for any program
14 shall be determined by the council and approved by a governing board
15 no later than the March 1 prior to the start of the academic year for
16 which the increase will first apply; and
17 7. As used in this paragraph:
18 a. "Continuous enrollment" means maintaining at least part-time
19 registration at the institution during the fall and spring semester
20 of each academic year;
21 b. "Mandatory student fee" means any fee or cost assessed to all
22 students enrolled in an institution or program of study that is not
23 tuition, including but not limited to any student recreation or
24 activity fee, student government fee, student health plan,
25 mandatory meal plan, facility fee, technology fee, or student-
26 endorsed fee; and
27 c. "Program" means an institution's undergraduate program or a
Page 3 of 11
XXXX 1/14/2026 10:22 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 77
1 specific graduate program. A student shall not be deemed to have
2 switched programs upon switching from one (1) undergraduate
3 major to another.
4 (b) In defining residency, the council shall classify a student as having Kentucky
5 residency if the student met the residency requirements at the beginning of his
6 or her last year in high school and enters a Kentucky postsecondary education
7 institution within two (2) years of high school graduation. In determining the
8 tuition for non-Kentucky residents, the council shall consider the fees required
9 of Kentucky students by institutions in adjoining states, the resident fees
10 charged by other states, the total actual per student cost of training in the
11 institutions for which the fees are being determined, and the ratios of
12 Kentucky students to non-Kentucky students comprising the enrollments of
13 the respective institutions, and other factors the council may in its sole
14 discretion deem pertinent, except that the Kentucky Community and
15 Technical College System may assess a mandatory student fee not to exceed
16 eight dollars ($8) per credit hour to be used exclusively for debt service on
17 amounts not to exceed seventy-five percent (75%) of the total projects cost of
18 the Kentucky Community and Technical College System agency bond
19 projects included in 2014 Ky. Acts ch. 117, Part II, J., 11.
20 (c)[(b)] The Kentucky Community and Technical College System mandatory fee
21 established in this subsection shall only be used for debt service on agency
22 bond projects.
23 (d)[(c)] Any fee established as provided by this subsection shall cease to be
24 assessed upon the retirement of the project bonds for which it services debt.
25 (e)[(d)] Prior to the issuance of any bonds, the Kentucky Community and
26 Technical College System shall certify in writing to the secretary of the
27 Finance and Administration Cabinet that sufficient funds have been raised to
Page 4 of 11
