1 meet the local match equivalent to twenty-five percent (25%) of the total
2 project cost;
3 (9) Devise, establish, and periodically review and revise policies to be used in making
4 recommendations to the Governor for consideration in developing
5 recommendations to the General Assembly for appropriations to the universities,
6 the Kentucky Community and Technical College System, and to support strategies
7 for persons to maintain necessary levels of literacy throughout their lifetimes. The
8 council has sole discretion, with advice of the Strategic Committee on
9 Postsecondary Education and the executive officers of the postsecondary education
10 system, to devise policies that provide for allocation of funds among the
11 universities and the Kentucky Community and Technical College System;
12 (10) Lead and provide staff support for the biennial budget process as provided under
13 KRS Chapter 48, in cooperation with the committee;
14 (11) (a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection, review and approve all
15 capital construction projects covered by KRS 45.750(1)(f), including real
16 property acquisitions, and regardless of the source of funding for projects or
17 acquisitions. Approval of capital projects and real property acquisitions shall
18 be on a basis consistent with the strategic agenda and the mission of the
19 respective universities and the Kentucky Community and Technical College
20 System.
21 (b) The organized groups that are establishing community college satellites as
22 branches of existing community colleges in the counties of Laurel, Leslie, and
23 Muhlenberg, and that have substantially obtained cash, pledges, real property,
24 or other commitments to build the satellite at no cost to the Commonwealth,
25 other than operating costs that shall be paid as part of the operating budget of
26 the main community college of which the satellite is a branch, are authorized
27 to begin construction of the satellite on or after January 1, 1998;
