1 (12) Require reports from the executive officer of each institution it deems necessary for
2 the effectual performance of its duties;
3 (13) Ensure that the state postsecondary system does not unnecessarily duplicate
4 services and programs provided by private postsecondary institutions and shall
5 promote maximum cooperation between the state postsecondary system and private
6 postsecondary institutions. Receive and consider an annual report prepared by the
7 Association of Independent Kentucky Colleges and Universities stating the
8 condition of independent institutions, listing opportunities for more collaboration
9 between the state and independent institutions and other information as appropriate;
10 (14) Establish course credit, transfer, and degree components as required in KRS
11 164.2951;
12 (15) (a) Define and approve the offering of all postsecondary education technical,
13 associate, baccalaureate, graduate, and professional degree, certificate, or
14 diploma programs in the public postsecondary education institutions. The
15 council shall not approve a new degree, certificate, or diploma program that
16 includes a requirement for a course or training of which the primary purpose
17 is to indoctrinate participants with a discriminatory concept.
18 (b) The council shall expedite wherever possible the approval of requests from
19 the Kentucky Community and Technical College System board of regents
20 relating to new certificate, diploma, technical, or associate degree programs of
21 a vocational-technical and occupational nature. Without the consent of the
22 General Assembly, the council shall not abolish or limit the total enrollment
23 of the general program offered at any community college to meet the goal of
24 reasonable access throughout the Commonwealth to a two (2) year course of
25 general studies designed for transfer to a baccalaureate program. This does not
26 restrict or limit the authority of the council, as set forth in this section, to
27 eliminate or make changes in individual programs within that general
