UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 77
1 KRS 161.028;
2 (21) Constitute the representative agency of the Commonwealth in all matters of
3 postsecondary education of a general and statewide nature which are not otherwise
4 delegated to one (1) or more institutions of postsecondary learning. The
5 responsibility may be exercised through appropriate contractual relationships with
6 individuals or agencies located within or without the Commonwealth. The authority
7 includes but is not limited to contractual arrangements for programs of research,
8 specialized training, and cultural enrichment;
9 (22) Maintain procedures for the approval of a designated receiver to provide for the
10 maintenance of student records of the public institutions of higher education and the
11 colleges as defined in KRS 164.945, and institutions operating pursuant to KRS
12 165A.310 which offer collegiate level courses for academic credit, which cease to
13 operate. Procedures shall include assurances that, upon proper request, subject to
14 federal and state laws and regulations, copies of student records shall be made
15 available within a reasonable length of time for a minimum fee;
16 (23) Monitor and transmit a report on compliance with KRS 164.351 to the director of
17 the Legislative Research Commission for distribution to the Interim Joint
18 Committee on Families and Children;
19 (24) (a) Develop in cooperation with each public university and the Kentucky
20 Community and Technical College System a comprehensive orientation and
21 education program for new members of the council and the governing boards
22 and continuing education opportunities for all council and board members.
23 For new members of the council and institutional governing boards, the
24 council shall:
25 1. Ensure that the orientation and education program comprises six (6)
26 hours of instruction time and includes but is not limited to information
27 concerning the roles of the council and governing board members, the
