1 (27) Employ consultants and other persons and employees as may be required for the
2 council's operations, functions, and responsibilities;
3 (28) Promulgate administrative regulations, in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A,
4 governing its powers, duties, and responsibilities as described in this section;
5 (29) Prepare and present by January 31 of each year an annual status report on
6 postsecondary education in the Commonwealth to the Governor, the Strategic
7 Committee on Postsecondary Education, and the Legislative Research Commission;
8 (30) Consider the role, function, and capacity of independent institutions of
9 postsecondary education in developing policies to meet the immediate and future
10 needs of the state. When it is found that independent institutions can meet state
11 needs effectively, state resources may be used to contract with or otherwise assist
12 independent institutions in meeting these needs;
13 (31) Create advisory groups representing the presidents, faculty, nonteaching staff, and
14 students of the public postsecondary education system and the independent colleges
15 and universities;
16 (32) Develop a statewide policy to promote employee and faculty development in state
17 and locally operated secondary area technology centers through the waiver of
18 tuition for college credit coursework in the public postsecondary education system.
19 Any regular full-time employee of a state or locally operated secondary area
20 technology center may, with prior administrative approval of the course offering
21 institution, take a maximum of six (6) credit hours per term at any public
22 postsecondary institution. The institution shall waive the tuition up to a maximum
23 of six (6) credit hours per term. The employee shall complete the Free Application
24 for Federal Student Aid to determine the level of need and eligibility for state and
25 federal financial aid programs. The amount of tuition waived shall not exceed the
26 cost of tuition at the institution less any state or federal grants received, which shall
27 be credited first to the student's tuition;
Page 10 of 11
