UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 77
1 (33) Participate with the Kentucky Department of Education, the Kentucky Board of
2 Education, and postsecondary education institutions to ensure that academic content
3 requirements for successful entry into postsecondary education programs are
4 aligned with high school content standards and that students who master the high
5 school academic content standards shall not need remedial courses. The council
6 shall monitor the results on an ongoing basis;
7 (34) Cooperate with the Kentucky Department of Education and the Education
8 Professional Standards Board in providing information sessions to selected
9 postsecondary education content faculty and teacher educators of the high school
10 academic content standards as required under KRS 158.6453(2)(l);
11 (35) Cooperate with the Office of the Kentucky Center for Statistics and ensure the
12 participation of the public institutions as required in KRS 151B.133;
13 (36) Pursuant to KRS 63.080, review written notices from the Governor or from a board
14 of trustees or board of regents concerning removal of a board member or the entire
15 appointed membership of a board, investigate the member or board and the conduct
16 alleged to support removal, and make written recommendations to the Governor
17 and the Legislative Research Commission as to whether the member or board
18 should be removed; and
19 (37) Exercise any other powers, duties, and responsibilities necessary to carry out the
20 purposes of this chapter. Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to grant the
21 Council on Postsecondary Education authority to disestablish or eliminate any
22 college of law which became a part of the state system of higher education through
23 merger with a state college.
24 Section 2. This Act may be cited as the Kentucky Student Tuition Protection
25 and Accountability Act.
26 Section 3. This Act takes effect July 1, 2029.
